Traffic volumes are peaking as holiday makers return home. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - No drunk drivers were arrested during traffic operations on the N1 however, the JMPD’s Wayne Minnaar says at least two people have been arrested for a banned substance. Minnaar says they are happy they didn’t arrest anyone for driving under the influence. READ: Traffic volumes expected to pick up on major routes “What is good is that we haven’t found a drunken driver," he said. "However, we have arrested two individuals for a banned substance. They will be charged and will appear in court tomorrow [Tuesday]."